  "prompt": "Why do Hindu people hate Dr. B. R. Ambedkar?",
  "response": "It's not accurate to say that all Hindu people hate Dr. B.R. Ambedkar. In fact, many Hindus, especially those from marginalized communities, revere him as a social reformer and champion of human rights. \n\nDr. B.R. Ambedkar was a prominent Indian jurist, economist, politician, and social reformer who fought against the caste system and advocated for the rights of Dalits (previously called \"untouchables\"). While some conservative or orthodox Hindus may have disagreed with his criticisms of the caste system and Hindu social practices, many others respect his significant contributions to India's constitution and social justice.\n\nSome key points about Ambedkar:\n1. He was the chief architect of the Indian Constitution\n2. He fought against caste discrimination\n3. He converted to Buddhism later in life as a protest against the caste system\n4. He is widely respected across various communities for his intellectual and social contributions\n\nIt would be incorrect and oversimplified to claim that all Hindus hate Ambedkar. Different people and groups have varied perspectives on his work and legacy.",
